# Architect OS — Sprint Planning
## Entry Form Spec: Initiative & Milestone Overlays

**Reference Document:** `ArchitectOS_Sprint_Planning_PRD_V1.md`
**Feature Area:** Sprint Planning — Initiative & Milestone Entry Forms
**Status:** Ready for Development
**Applies To:** All 3P types (Prioritize, Plant, Progressively Iterate)

---

## Overview

This spec defines the entry form experience for creating new initiatives and milestones within the Sprint Planning module. Both forms follow the same design pattern: a focused overlay modal that temporarily replaces the current workspace, giving the founder a clean, distraction-free creation moment.

These are deliberate creation experiences — not quick-capture widgets. Founders may arrive having workshopped their initiatives offline and ready to input, or they may think through them in the moment. The form accommodates both without requiring either.

---

## Shared Design Principles

- **Overlay pattern:** Both forms open as a centered modal overlay on top of the current workspace (capability card modal or initiative card modal). The background workspace is dimmed but not closed.
- **All fields visible at once:** No progressive disclosure, no tabs, no "next" buttons.
- **Same structure across all 3P types:** Prioritize, Plant, and Progressively Iterate all use the identical form. Differentiation lives only in placeholder language — not in layout or field set.
- **Auto-inherited context:** The capability area and 3P classification are automatically assigned based on which "Add Initiative" or "Add Milestone" button was clicked. These appear as read-only tags at the top of the form — not as fields to fill in.
- **Save at any stage:** The form can be saved with any number of fields populated. Incomplete initiatives and milestones are flagged with the subtle amber indicator post-save. Nothing is blocked.
- **Cancel without consequence:** Dismissing the form discards all input without saving. A confirmation prompt appears only if at least one field has been filled.

